      },
      "components": [],
      "subtasks": [],
      "created": "2013-03-01T19:22:08.964+0000",
      "description": "If the NM is shutdown in a non-clean manner, the containers launched by it will remain running. When a NM is brought up, there needs to be some handling to ensure that the node is clean before new containers can be launched on it. \n\nSpecial care should be taken to handle cases where the PIDs wrap around - it may be non-trivial to figure out if the process running currently actually maps to the previously launched container.",
